<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=254&amp;p=1672#p1672"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />5: It would wrap around after $3FFF.  For $2006 register writes you could discard the upper address bits.<br /></div><br /><br />With $2006 writes, you MUST discard (clear, actually) the upper address bits - if this did not happen, it would be possible to to mid-screen smooth vertical scrolling without using special tricks.<br />On $2007 accesses, however, it appears to increment it from $3FFF to $4000 (which would be $0000 for VRAM accesses, but $000 with YSCROLL=4 for rendering); some testing needs to be done with this...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Mar 23, 2005 12:44 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
